Patch Set 6:

I'm re-raising the discussion again for the LOG level since seems we have not gotten an agreement on that. markwash's comments triggered me rethink it. As for the log level, I think it should depend on the view/perspective of 'user'. Cloud administrator/deployer should be the consumer of the log, so it makes more sense for me to log it as debug/info level because the quota exceeding is most like a normal scenario instead of a warning. As you see, I'm adjusting my opinion on this :) Sorry about back and forth.

Patch Set 6:

The value in it for me as an admin of a cloud is in knowing that users are bumping against their limits during log analysis. Debug for sure doesn't give me that since I never run a production box with debug enabled due to the sheer amount of logs. Info may make sense, but not debug.

Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Had a quick chat with sdague today about this. He emphasized to me that the main goal is to make sure these types of messages aren't treated as ERROR level logs. My vote is bumped up to INFO level, since I still think of WARN as something that "Indicates that there might be a systemic issue; potential predictive failure notice" as at https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards and I don't see how hitting your quota fits that description.

tl;dr: I think these messages should be pushed to INFO.

Thanks!
